### Get current model

#   The model field is required by the spec but the loaded model is always
#   used regardless — use GET /v1/models to get the exact ID of whatever is
#   currently loaded.

GET http://127.0.0.1:42069/v1/models

###  Ask a simple question


POST http://127.0.0.1:42069/v1/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
   "model": "Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC",
   "messages": [
       { "role": "user", "content": "What is the capital of France?" }
     ]
}


###


POST http://127.0.0.1:42069/v1/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
   "model": "Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC",
   "messages": [
       { "role": "user", "content": "What is WebGPU?" }
     ]
}


### Streaming


POST http://127.0.0.1:42069/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
   "model": "Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC",
   "messages": [
     { "role": "user", "content": "Tell me a haiku about local AI." }
   ],
   "stream": true
}


### With System Prompt  

POST http://127.0.0.1:42069/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
   "model": "Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC",
   "messages":
    [
      { "role": "system",    "content": "You are a concise assistant."},
      { "role": "user",      "content": "What is WebGPU?" }
    ],
   "temperature": 0.7,
   "max_tokens": 2048
}

### Multi-turn with system prompt,

POST http://127.0.0.1:42069/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
   "model": "Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC",
   "messages":
    [
      { "role": "system",    "content": "You are a concise assistant."},
      { "role": "user",      "content": "What is WebGPU?" },
      { "role": "assistant", "content": "WebGPU is a modern GPU API for the web." },
      { "role": "user",      "content": "How does it compare to WebGL?" }
    ],
   "temperature": 0.7,
   "max_tokens": 2048
}


